Suspended ANC Western Cape chairperson Marius Fransman held a press conference at the ANC's offices on Monday, following a finding by the party's national disciplinary appeals committee that his case of alleged sexual assault be referred back to the national disciplinary committee. Fransman had complained that his disciplinary process was unfair because the committee had failed to take into consideration evidence of two witnesses in his case.   To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
